name: Nikola Jokic
tip: Finished the best player in fantasy basketball for the past 2 seasons, and he'll continue being one of the best big men in fantasy basketball for years to come.

name: Kevin Durant
tip: KD will be KD no matter where he plays.

name: Joel Embiid
tip: Can he follow up his MVP-like season with another? He'll continue to put up elite numbers. Just don't expect him to play a full season.

name: James Harden
tip: Harden didn't look great during the playoffs, but he rarely does. An off-season working the pick-and-roll with Embiid should only mean good things for next season.

name: Giannis Antetokounmpo
tip: If you have Giannis on your roster you're most likely punting FT%, and for your team build, he's the #1 player in fantasy.

name: LeBron James
tip: Never doubt LeBron James, but he's 37.

name: Stephen Curry
tip: Steph is no longer somebody you can rely on for solid FG%, and it has cost him a few spots in the rankings. Don't fret, he's still an elite fantasy player.

name: Karl-Anthony Towns
tip: Gobert will eat into his rebounding, shot blocking, and touches at the rim, but he's still an uber-efficient shooter at the C position who can hit 2+ 3s a game.

name: Kyrie Irving
tip: Rosters always look better when Kyrie is on them, but it's hard to trust him to stay motivated enough to play basketball for an entire season.

name: Luka Doncic
tip: His counting stats are elite, and his defensive numbers are starting to look respectable. We're going to see sky-high usage from Luka now that Porzingis is off the roster.

name: Trae Young
tip: I don't see the addition of Murray hurting Trae's dynasty value all that much.

name: Damian Lillard
tip: I'm expecting Lillard to bounce back after having time off to recover from his injury.

name: Anthony Davis
tip: The last time Davis played over 62 games in a season he was wearing a New Orleans jersey (2017-18). He's obviously an elite talent when he plays, but we can't ignore how many games he has missed, and is set to continue missing.

name: Jayson Tatum
tip: We last saw Tatum on the court having a less than Tatum-like finals series (says the still bitter Celtics fan), but fantasy basketball is a regular-season game.

name: Tyrese Haliburton
tip: Haliburton averaged 17.5 points, 9.6 assists, 1.8 steals, and 2.2 3PM on 50.2% shooting from the field and 84.9% from the line in his 26 games in Indiana this season. They're elite numbers, and Tyrese is on his way to becoming an elite player.

name: LaMelo Ball
tip: Has a fantasy-friendly game and is in the perfect low-pressure, fast-paced scenario in Charlotte.

name: Kawhi Leonard
tip: He'll be back next season, but it's hard to trust him to play enough games to win you a championship.

name: Devin Booker
tip: Booker closed out the season strong as he upped his usage to cover for an injured CP3, finishing the season as the 21st best player (based on per-game rankings).

name: Paul George
tip: He's back and relatively healthy with something to prove heading into next season.

name: Jimmy Butler
tip: Butler hasn't played more than 58 games since his 2018-19 season (when he played for Minnesota and Philadelphia). He'll be 33 next season, and hasn't shown signs of having a reliable 3-point shot since, coincidently, his 2018-19 season (which was the last time he averaged 1 3-point make per game).

name: Khris Middleton
tip: Middleton is back to his regular self after a slow start to the season, which was expected after a lack of off-season (extended playoffs, Olympics).

name: Bam Adebayo
tip: We know Bam is capable of averaging 5 assists a game when the ball runs through him on the offensive end, but how much of his career he'll be asked to play that role?

name: Kristaps Porzingis
tip: Porzingis will always be the guy with an injury cloud hovering over him, so you're never going to get a fair return when trading him if you're looking at per-game value, but when he plays, he's putting up top-40 value.

name: DeMar DeRozan
tip: I was expecting DeRozan's value to take a hit moving to Chicago, but he's having the best fantasy season of his career (so far).

name: Chris Paul
tip: If you have Paul in a dynasty format now's the time to try and move him, unless you're competing for the title.

name: Domantas Sabonis
tip: His assists went back up to 5.8 a game in Sacramento, and he'll have a full off-season to re-adust with his new team.

name: Shai Gilgeous-Alexander
tip: When Shai plays, he's great, but how many games will Shai play this season?

name: Fred VanVleet
tip: He's somebody who can help you win a championship if you can stomach his FG%.

name: Robert Williams
tip: I'd be lying if I said I wasn't concerned about how much playing injured during the playoffs is going to impact his knees long-term. He'd be ranked a lot higher otherwise.

name: Darius Garland
tip: Garland's usage might take a small dip this season, but dynasty is a long-term game.

name: Jrue Holiday
tip: He's back to playing at an elite level and has minimal competition at either of the guard spots in Milwaukee.

name: Myles Turner
tip: Indiana finally cleared up their Sabonis-Turner situation by moving Sabonis, but we haven't stopped hearing Turner trade rumors ever since.

name: Rudy Gobert
tip: His rebounding will take a hit playing next to another capable rebounder, but he's still going to be an elite 3-category monster.

name: Bradley Beal
tip: Beal has had a season to forget but still finished the season as the 48th ranked player based on per-game value. Somebody to target in a trade if you're retooling for next season.

name: Jarrett Allen
tip: Cleveland's big starting lineup on paper caps Allen's upside, but, in reality, it's bringing the best out of him.

name: Ja Morant
tip: Morant bounced back after a season to forget and cemented himself as a high-end fantasy player.

name: Zach LaVine
tip: A healthy Chicago team means less usage for LaVine. But a fully healthy Chicago is something we haven't seen much of.

name: Donovan Mitchell
tip: We're going to see a re-motivated Mitchell this season, but he's no longer the lone man on the offensive end.

name: Terry Rozier
tip: Proved a lot of people wrong last season and locked himself in as the 2-guard option to play alongside LaMelo. He might not be able to replicate last season's production, but he'll get close.

name: Pascal Siakam
tip: The Siakam experience can be shaky, but the pressure is off him to be Toronto's best player, and his fantasy game has benefitted.

name: Nikola Vucevic
tip: His points and rebound numbers are still impressive, but he's starting to trend down as a high-end fantasy player.

name: Deandre Ayton
tip: A lot of people are low on Ayton, but he still finished in the top 50 last season after a "bad" season.

name: Desmond Bane
tip: A knock-down shooter who's on pace to become a fantasy staple.

name: Anthony Edwards
tip: He continues to blossom into a star in the league. At this point, the only thing holding him back is his FG%.

name: Cade Cunningham
tip: Cade had an excellent rookie season, finishing as the 59th best player based on per-game averages. The FG% is a worry, but it's hard to imagine it not improving over the next few seasons.

name: Dejounte Murray
tip: Moving to Atlanta hurts his value as he finds himself playing with a ball-dominant guard and bigs who can rebound.

name: Jaren Jackson Jr
tip: Right when we start getting excited about JJJ's season, he gets injured again, and it's a pattern I'm not down for.
injury: Expected to be out until at least Nov 1

name: Jaylen Brown
tip: His usage increased a little more than expected last season, and there's nothing to suggest that he can't continue it. Just needs to keep improving his FT%.

name: Jonas Valanciunas
tip: Now's a great time to try and flip Jonas if you can find somebody willing to give up a top 20-30 guy. His value will take a hit if/when Zion returns, but he's still more than capable of producing along side of him.

name: Kyle Lowry
tip: Joining Miami lowers his production, but how many more seasons does he have left in him?

name: Evan Mobley
tip: Mobley has the signs of being a generational talent on the defensive end of the floor, and he's more than capable of scoring on the other end of the floor. If his FT% can reach the 70% range then we're looking at a promising second season.

name: John Collins
tip: He'll continue to put up top-55 numbers that are propped up because of his shooting efficiency from the field and the free-throw line. We know what he's capable of if he's more of a focus on the offensive end, but that won't happen unless he finds himself on another roster.

name: Jordan Poole
tip: He has increased his scoring from last season (from 12 points to 18.5) and assists (from 1.9 to 4) as he spent a lot of the season either covering for an injured Klay or Steph, but he needs to show more on the defensive end to make up for the small dip in playing time he might see next season with a healthy Warriors roster.

name: De'Aaron Fox
tip: Sacramento moving Haliburton means they're fully invested in Fox at PG. Should mesh well with Sabonis with an off-season under their belt.

name: Scottie Barnes
tip: Remember when everybody was worried that Toronto reached for Barnes in the draft?

name: Mikal Bridges
tip: I like what Mikal provides long-term as a 3&D specialist, and his offensive production has started trending in the right direction.

name: CJ McCollum
tip: In the past, he has been streaky in terms of output and FG%. Try and flip him when he goes on a stretch where he puts up top-40 value and shoots 45%+ from the field.

name: Tyrese Maxey
tip: Maxey has proved that he belongs as a big minute rotation player. His assist numbers won't hit big numbers with Harden around, but he makes up for it by giving you high-end FG% from the PG spot.

name: Gordon Hayward
tip: He's going to continue putting up good numbers with Bridges out, but, meh.

name: Michael Porter Jr
tip: His value is tied to how efficiently he shoots, and when his shot isn't falling, like it didn't last season, then his value tanks.

name: PJ Washington
tip: It looks like PJ will claim back the starting PF spot in Charlotte. The last time he started at PF for a season (2020-21), he averaged 12.9 points, 6.5 rebounds, 1.1 steals, 1.2 blocks, and 1.8 3PM.

name: Jamal Murray
tip: Murray should be back to start the season after missing the entire regular season. Keep in mind that he finished the 2020-21 season averaging 21.2 points, 4.8 assists, 1.3 steals, and 2.7 3PM, while shooting 47.8% from the field and 86.8% from the line.

name: Julius Randle
tip: His numbers have regressed to pre-Knicks Randle, but he has started to kick into gear these past few weeks, so there's still hope for a revival.

name: Brandon Ingram
tip: His lack of defensive numbers hurt his value.

name: Draymond Green
tip: Golden State is a playoff team again, so we're seeing top-60 Draymond again.

name: Tyler Herro
tip: He should have the 6th man award guaranteed as he finishes the season as the 67th best fantasy player based on per-game value.

name: OG Anunoby
tip: Has the potential to be a top-50 staple as he continues to develop his game.

name: Devin Vassell
tip: Has a touch of the Mikal Bridges about him as a defensive-minded 3-point shooter. If he's somehow still on your waiver wire, go and add him now.

name: D'Angelo Russell
tip: His fantasy game is starting to regress and other players are becoming better options. Still has value in the right build.

name: Ivica Zubac
tip: Is capable of being a top 120 player when given the minutes, but his upside is capped with Ibaka's ability to play C.

name: Onyeka Okongwu
tip: He's too good of a player not to get the opportunity to start; whether that's next season or the season after, the talent to be a high-end fantasy player is there.

name: Zion Williamson
tip: His upside is huge (no, that wasn't a pun about his weight). but he has missed significant time every season since joining the NBA. He's almost off his rookie contract without a healthy season in the books and has only played 85-games in his first 3 seasons.

name: Jerami Grant
tip: He won't need to be the scorer that he was in Detroit, but his efficiency should bounce back playing in an offense that's capable of generating good looks at the basket.

name: Wendell Carter Jr
tip: Gets a chance to revive his career in Orlando, and he's meeting expectations so far.

name: Tobias Harris
tip: A lot of Harris' value was tied to the fact that he doesn't hurt you in any one category, but, this season he's hurting you in a few, mainly FG%.

name: Lauri Markkanen
tip: The fit in Cleveland doesn't look great on paper, but it's working so far.

name: Keegan Murray
tip: The Kings copped a lot of flack with this pick (because Kangz), but Murray put up elite numbers in Iowa (23.5 points, 8.7 rebounds, 1.3 steals, 1.9 blocks). He needs to work on his play making ability, but it's ok if that isn't part of his game for now because the rest of his game is there.

name: Marcus Smart
tip: It seems like Smart has returned to his old punt-FG ways, but his steals, 3s, and assists make up for it.

name: Al Horford
tip: It feels like Horford will get the occasional start at C for Boston this season as they prepare to go one step further and win a championship.

name: Gary Trent Jr
tip: Has found a role in Toronto, but I'm not sure how long his steal numbers are going to remain this high.

name: Jalen Brunson
tip: His FG% is surprisingly efficient for a short point-guard (50.2% last season).

name: Jakob Poeltl
tip: Nobody is standing in the way of Poeltl playing 30 minutes a night in San Antonio, but his FT% continues to be an issue. He feels like more of a stop-gap solution rather than a long-term one.

name: Ben Simmons
tip: His game hasn't changed since entering the league, and there's nothing to suggest that anything will change this season. At this stage, he is what he is, and that's a guy who can give you great out-of-position stats (FG%, REB) for a PG-eligible player (when he eventually steps back on the court).

name: Alperen Sengun
tip: The Wood trade opens up playing time at the PF and C spots for Sengun and whichever big man they select at 3 in the draft. In the 11 games Wood missed last season, Sengun averaged 29.2 minutes, 13.2 points, 8.7 rebounds, and 3.5 assists.

name: Keldon Johnson
tip: The potential is there to be a 20 point-per-game scorer, but his defensive numbers need to improve before he takes the next step as a fantasy player.

name: Brook Lopez
tip: Brook has found a way to extend his career as a 3-point sniper, but how long can he keep it up?

name: Franz Wagner
tip: Landed in a good spot in Orlando and should continue to expand on his fantasy game in a low-pressure environment.

name: Saddiq Bey
tip: He continues to bomb your FG%, best suited in the right punt build.

name: Robert Covington
tip: Name a more iconic duo than Robert Covington starting the season slow and then ending the season as a top-70 guy.

name: Kelly Olynyk
tip: He'll spend time backing up both Grant and Stewart this season and still be close to putting up top-100 value in re-draft leagues.

name: Lonzo Ball
tip: The move to Chicago matches his skillset as somebody who can run the break, play defense, and not worry about looking for his own shot inside the 3-point line, but there's a lot of ball-handling in the starting roster with LaVine, DeRozan, and Vucevic all capable passers. His re-draft rankings are currently propped up by his career-high steal rate.
injury: Expected to be out until at least Jan 2

name: Klay Thompson
tip: Klay is back. That's all that matters.

name: Isaiah Hartenstein
tip: Puts up nice numbers when he plays over 20 minutes a game, but he's in a timeshare with Robinson.

name: Jabari Smith Jr
tip: He's going to get heavy minutes in Houston and he's a decent enough defender to pair along side Sengun. My only worry is his FG% for somebody at the PF spot (42.9% in his most recent year in college), and how that's going to translate playing in a team like Houston.

name: Paolo Banchero
tip: There's every chance he'll win rookie of the year as he fills a need Orlando are desperate for (scoring). At some point this season he'll have people questioning why he didn't go number 1 in some dynasty rookie drafts.

name: Christian Wood
tip: I think his value stays the same moving to Dallas, who are desperate for a consistent scoring threat at the PF/C spot.

name: Monte Morris
tip: A healthy Murray eats into his minutes next season.

name: Josh Giddey
tip: If he can clean up his shooting percentages he's a chance of becoming a really nice fantasy player. Should have ample opportunity in OKC to collect those counting stats.

name: Jusuf Nurkic
tip: Is Nurkic really just a guy capable of putting up top 60-70 value in 25-27 minutes a game?

name: Mike Conley
tip: He is what he is (an aging PG who'll hover around the 90-110 range in re-draft leagues for a few more seasons).

name: JaVale McGee
tip: Is McGee really going to start in Dallas next season?

name: Kevin Porter Jr
tip: Only fits very specific punt builds (or points leagues) due to his horrible shooting percentages.

name: Jarred Vanderbilt
tip: The PF spot is wide open in Utah. We know what he can do defensively, but can he start contributing on the offensive end and score more than 7 points a game?

name: Jalen Smith
tip: Can we trust Indiana enough to think that he's actually going to start at PF next season?

name: Clint Capela
tip: The opportunity to get Capela for a good deal is closing as he works his way back to full health.

name: Bobby Portis
tip: Tucker leaving Milwaukee provides Portis with the opportunity to play a bigger role this season.

name: Buddy Hield
tip: Buddy averaged 18.2 points, 5.1 rebounds, 4.8 assists, and 3.1 3PM in his 26 games in a Pacers uniform.

name: Kyle Kuzma
tip: Is exceeding expectations so far this season and he suddenly finds himself as Washington's go-to guy with Beal out for the rest of the season.

name: Cameron Johnson
tip: Is showing some promise as a backup stretch-4 and could find himself as a fringe-starter soon.

name: Bogdan Bogdanovic
tip: Has a well-rounded fantasy game, but Atlanta is already stacked at SG/SF, so his upside is capped.

name: Jalen Green
tip: A great athlete whose offensive game is well suited to the NBA. It's going to take time, and he's going to tank your FG% in the process, but the potential is there.

name: Caleb Martin
tip: The twin that can hit free-throws. Not much upside.

name: Nicolas Claxton
tip: Next season looks to be the season for Claxton, and he has shown enough to be worthy of more minutes, but I'm not sure that's what Brooklyn has in mind for him this season (hopefully it's not history repeating itself).

name: Anfernee Simons
tip: Portland is fully invested in Simons, and so am I. Should be able to replicate CJ's output now that he's gone.

name: Spencer Dinwiddie
tip: Cuban gave up a lot just to bring in somebody to talk crypto with.

name: Cody Martin
tip: The twin that played more games. Still has the same low upside.

name: Bones Hyland
tip: The guy can score, but, realistically, he's an undersized SG. Will be a nice bench scorer though.

name: Kendrick Nunn
tip: His role won't be big enough in LA to be somebody to roster in most formats.

name: Malcolm Brogdon
tip: His value takes a hit moving to Boston, but it might mean we'll get a semi-healthy season from him.

name: Brandon Clarke
tip: JJJ missing time again should give Clarke an avenue to more minutes to start the season, but we saw in the playoffs that playing Adams was a liability, so hopefully, that means Memphis try playing JJJ and Clarke together more this season.

name: Daniel Gafford
tip: Porzingis eats into his chances of being a productive fantasy player, but Porzingis has a habit of missing games. Best case scenario has Gafford on another roster next season.

name: Mitchell Robinson
tip: Thibs has managed to teach Robinson not to bite on every blocked shot attempt, and it helped him stay on the court for a little longer by avoiding foul trouble. He'll still give you the big man stats you're looking for, just don't expect his huge block rate from his rookie season to return this season.

name: Norman Powell
tip: Don't expect much outside of his shooting stats (PTS and 3PM on solid shooting %s).

name: Aaron Gordon
tip: The days of waiting for Gordon to become fantasy relevant again are past us.

name: Patrick Williams
tip: His defensive game is going to lock him in for 25+ minutes a game, but his usage won't be high enough to make him fantasy relevant unless he can improve his fantasy numbers.

name: Harrison Barnes
tip: Like clockwork, Barnes starts the season hot and then cools down.

name: De'Anthony Melton
tip: Seems set to continue playing 24-28 minutes as a backup, but that's enough for him to be rosterable.

name: Otto Porter Jr
tip: The days of Otto being a fantasy-relevant player have passed us.

name: Kentavious Caldwell-Pope
tip: No upside, but he's a good streaming option if you need some 3s.

name: Andrew Wiggins
tip: Is Wiggins starting to finally work into Golden States system? Not a whole lot of upside with Klay eventually returning and Golden State drafting 2 rookies in the lottery who also play his position.

name: Cole Anthony
tip: It's debatable whether he's a starter on a good team or a solid bench scorer, but his minutes should be similar in either role.

name: Richaun Holmes
tip: Sacramento is capable of doing anything, but I'm going to assume he plays backup minutes at PF/C this season.

name: Matisse Thybulle
tip: A defensive stud who proved he has a 3-point shot in the Olympics. Will we see it in the NBA?

name: Isaiah Stewart
tip: He's a good high-energy guy who gives you an impact on the defensive end, but he needs to develop his offensive game if he wants to find himself as a staple on dynasty rosters. I can see him being more of a stop-gap until a better option arrives (like Duren).

name: Jalen Suggs
tip: Orlando is deep at the PG spot, and while he's had a poor start to the season, it's not uncommon for PGs to take a while to adapt to running an NBA offense. He'll be better than this.

name: Bojan Bogdanovic
tip: He can score, and he's doing that in Utah, but he doesn't offer much else. Still has value for a season or two, so long as his shot continues to fall.

name: Mo Bamba
tip: It looks like the 2C tandem is out next season, and Bamba is likely looking at a backup role.

name: Dillon Brooks
tip: His FG% will hurt you given the volume of shots that he takes. Not a bad option to have at the end of your roster, but there's not much growth left in his game.

name: Bruce Brown
tip: Is doing some nice things in Brooklyn, but the upside isn't there.

name: Patrick Beverley
tip: Looks like his days of being a fringe starter are past him. He doesn't have much upside in the fantasy format as an end-of-roster guy, and not something to target for anything long-term.

name: Nassir Little
tip: Still very raw, but he has shown enough to be a rotation player next season.

name: Jaden McDaniels
tip: Needs to expand and continue to develop his outside shot to cement a spot in the starting lineup.

name: Alex Caruso
tip: Can't see him being anything more than a backup, but he can produce when given the minutes.

name: Derrick White
tip: Moving to Boston hurts his numbers a little, and the addition of Brogdon doesn't help, either.

name: Markelle Fultz
tip: The addition of Suggs dampens his ability to become a top-100 player again since it caps his assists (one of his few positive categories). Maybe with the spotlight off him, he might start to expand his scoring a little more?
injury: Expected to be out until at least Nov 1

name: Collin Sexton
tip: At this point, we need to stop looking at Sexton as a PG. He's a score-first combo-guard, who might be best suited in a 6th man role.

name: Jae'Sean Tate
tip: His defensive ability is good enough to keep him on the court, so anything he can produce on the other end is a bonus.

name: Kelly Oubre Jr
tip: Has more freedom on the offensive end in Charlotte and should continue playing starter-level minutes for the rest of the season.

name: Pat Connaughton
tip: Older than you think. Doesn't have much fantasy upside. He's a nice dunker, though.

name: Reggie Jackson
tip: An end of roster guy if you're looking for PG stats.

name: Luguentz Dort
tip: The guy is a defensive stud, and he has turned into a 3-point sniper on the offensive end, but his FG% is brutal, and his defensive numbers don't reflect his defensive ability.

name: Chuma Okeke
tip: Hasn't been able to replicate his stretch from last season, but he's still working his way back from injury.

name: Seth Curry
tip: His value is tied to being able to contribute 3s without hurting your FG%. If you don't need that, then you don't need Seth.

name: Kevin Huerter
tip: A nice end-of-roster guy who has a fresh start in Sacramento.

name: Mason Plumlee
tip: Name a more iconic duo than the Charlotte Hornets and white guys starting at center. Plumlee's passing game works well in Charlotte, but there are better options available.

name: Chris Duarte
tip: He was OK without doing anything above average, and should improve heading into next season.

name: Darius Bazley
tip: The starting PF spot in OKC is a rotating door right now, and with so many picks coming in it's hard to see him locking it down long term unless something major happens next season.

name: Jonathan Isaac
tip: How sure are we that he's still interested in playing basketball?

name: Jae Crowder
tip: Fills a need in Phoenix, but he's not somebody to expect fantasy production from.

name: Grayson Allen
tip: Capable of getting hot and finds himself as one of the few SGs on the roster. Has limited upside.

name: Andre Drummond
tip: Do we have any Drummond truthers still around?

name: Will Barton
tip: There should be better options available.

name: Caris LeVert
tip: Better suited to points leagues where his flakey shooting percentages won't hurt you.

name: Thomas Bryant
tip: Porzingis eats into any chance he had of being a productive fantasy player while wearing a Wizards jersey. Best case scenario he moves to another team in the off-season.

name: Immanuel Quickley
tip: He only has the size to play PG, but he's very useful off-the-ball and is a great shooter. Will continue to see playing time so long as his shot continues to fall, and should be a good gunner off the bench.

name: Malik Beasley
tip: The emergence of Anthony Edwards takes shots away from Beasley, and it has dramatically impacted his fantasy value.

name: Victor Oladipo
tip: I'm not sure how much longer Oladipo can keep running off the reputation of that one good season he had in Indiana, and it's looking more and more like an outlier once you see that he has only shot 44% or better from the field twice in his 8-season career. He'll start the season missing games so stash him on the IL and take a flyer on somebody on the waiver wire with upside.

name: Isaiah Jackson
tip: It seems like Indiana is interested in parting ways with Turner, and Jackson is next-in-line if that happens.

name: Grant Williams
tip: He's a high energy guy off the bench, but his ceiling is capped as a role player.

name: Steven Adams
tip: Not fantasy-relevant anymore unless you need to temporarily fill a gap at the C spot.

name: Aleksej Pokusevski
tip: One of the biggest boom/bust dynasty options in the NBA.

name: Tim Hardaway Jr
tip: His ceiling is capped, and it doesn't look like he'll be more than a contributor to the PTS, 3PM, and FT% categories.

name: Kevin Love
tip: Love is making a comeback, but he's still best suited as an end of bench guy on a team fighting for a championship.

name: RJ Barrett
tip: Better suited to points leagues unless you can deal with his poor shooting %s from the field and the line.

name: Killian Hayes
tip: Had one of the worst starts to a rookie campaign you can imagine, and his second season isn't looking all that great, but he's still in a good situation in Detroit to turn it around.

name: Quentin Grimes
tip: Seems like a very Thibs kind of player and could be somebody who works his way into the rotation as the season progresses.

name: Derrick Rose
tip: Still capable of scoring, but there should be better options available.

name: Kyle Anderson
tip: His role in Memphis has declined since last season, and with it, his dynasty value.

name: Delon Wright
tip: Moving to Atlanta was basically the worst-case scenario for Delon's fantasy production. He'll see some minutes at backup PG and SG, but not enough to be fantasy relevant unless Trae gets hurt.

name: Royce O'Neale
tip: His ceiling is being able to spot-start as a low usage defensive specialist.

name: Deni Avdija
tip: Hasn't shown signs of being an impactful fantasy player yet, but the opportunity for a bigger role is there for the rest of the season.

name: Cameron Payne
tip: Has proved himself to be a worthy backup in the NBA.

name: Bennedict Mathurin
tip: We saw Duarte get a lot of minutes in his rookie season, and I see Mathurin going down a similar path. Watch this space if Buddy Hield gets traded before the start of the season.

name: Jaxson Hayes
tip: Somebody to stash if you believe in his upside.
injury: Expected to be out until at least Oct 22

name: Tari Eason
tip: A great athlete who can put up fantasy numbers, but it's not ideal that he plays the same position as the person they invested a top-3 pick on.

name: Jordan Clarkson
tip: Has been running hot since moving to Utah, and it looks like it's sustainable, but he doesn't offer much outside of scoring categories.

name: Russell Westbrook
tip: After this season, it's hard to roster Westbrook in anything other than points leagues as I doubt many people are running with both a punt FG% and punt FT% build in 9-cat leagues.

name: Gorgui Dieng
tip: A streamer when he spot-starts, otherwise he's somebody you can avoid.

name: Gorgui Dieng
tip: A streamer when he spot-starts, otherwise he's somebody you can avoid.

name: Gorgui Dieng
tip: A streamer when he spot-starts, otherwise he's somebody you can avoid.

name: Gorgui Dieng
tip: A streamer when he spot-starts, otherwise he's somebody you can avoid.

name: Talen Horton-Tucker
tip: Has shown flashes of being a fantasy producer, but he'll need to be on another roster to fulfill it.

name: Tyus Jones
tip: His days of being a streamable bench player look to be past him.

name: Josh Richardson
tip: Is he's still riding off the reputation of that one good season in Miami?

name: Chet Holmgren
tip: There's still a case for taking Chet at #1 in a dynasty rookie draft and tanking for Wembanyama, but I won't talk you out of taking Banchero.

name: Jaden Ivey
tip: He's going to be a lot of fun to watch in transition. The offensive game is there, but he needs to produce more on the defensive end.

name: Jalen Duren
tip: I really like the fit in Detroit, I'm just worried that Casey (who isn't known for developing rookies) is going to Casey him.

name: Jonathan Kuminga
tip: He has shown signs of being a productive NBA player, but I'm not quite there with him just yet as a fantasy player. Cleaning up his FT% or showing the ability to tally defensive stats will propel his game to the next level if he can find 25+ minutes a game next season.

name: James Wiseman
tip: His value is low enough to take a flyer on during the off-season if the asking price is small enough.

name: Jalen Williams
tip: Has impressed so far in summer league, and should get rotation minutes, but OKC already has a lot of young talent to distribute minutes to.

name: Miles Bridges
tip: This is essentially a placeholder since it's hard to see him playing in the NBA any time soon.

name: Jeremy Sochan
tip: His outside shot needs work, but he's the high IQ type player that the Spurs love and he has great feel for the game.

name: Joshua Primo
tip: Has the tools to be a quality role player even at his age and should have an expanded role heading into next season.

name: Shaedon Sharpe
tip: I'd have Sharpe higher if he landed on another team. He's Portland's best asset to include in a package for a star player, but his time on the court is going to be pretty inconsistent in his rookie season so long as he stays in Portland. The upside is definitely there though.

name: Mark Williams
tip: I might have Williams a little too high, and he could very well be a bust in his rookie season with Charlotte not known for letting rookies play big minutes at C (because apparently Plumbee is just too good?), but the potential to be a Robert Williams / Mitchell Robinson type player is there.

name: Dyson Daniels
tip: He should have an impact in his rookie season as a ready-made defensive stud. His shot needs a lot of work.

name: Davion Mitchell
tip: He's too good of a defensive player not to give starter-level minutes to, and his stretch towards the end of the season (18.3 points, 7.9 assists across his last 14 games) has shown that he's more than capable of scoring. Can we trust the Kings not to mess this up?

name: Walker Kessler
tip: Some players put up great block numbers without actually being a great defender (hello Hassan Whiteside) and I have a feeling Kessler is going to be one of those players.

name: Jake LaRavia
tip: While he's not the most athletic guy out there (yes, he's white) he makes up for it with his positioning, passing, and shooting ability.

name: Moses Moody
tip: Moody is a great 3&D prospect, but might be one of those better-in-real-life-than-fantasy type players. He should crack the rotation this season with Golden State a little short on bench rotation players.

name: Obi Toppin
tip: The fit with Randle isn't great, but he has the potential to fill a role as a gunner off the bench.

name: Jalen Johnson
tip: A great athlete who can give you great defensive numbers, but Atlanta is already deep at the PF spot. Somebody to stash for the long term.

name: Malik Monk
tip: Is there enough minutes in Sacramento at SG for Monk, Mitchell, and Huerter?

name: AJ Griffin
tip: Hats off to Atlanta, because they keep on drafting guys that I really like, but they keep on drafting players who play in an already deep position, and AJ is no exception. He's already a great shooter (44.7% from 3 in college), and a good rebounder for his position. He needs work defensively, but most rookies who aren't defensive specialists do.

name: Marvin Bagley III
tip: Marvin is finally out of Sacramento and into one of the lowest pressure environments in the league. It's just unfortunate that he plays the same position as one of Detroit's best players.
injury: Expected to be out until at least Nov 2

name: Coby White
tip: His output this season is going to take a dive with the additions to Chicago's roster (Lonzo, DeMar, and Caruso). I wouldn't blame you for moving on from him.

name: De'Andre Hunter
tip: Maybe he peaked during his 2020-21 season, but it's always worth keeping an eye on a young player getting 30-minutes of playing time a game.

name: Ziaire Williams
tip: Has a nice all-around game, but needs to continue putting in work to fight for a starting spot in the future.

name: Rui Hachimura
tip: He's still a little raw, but he's one of the best young players on the roster, so he'll continue to see minutes.

name: Josh Hart
tip: Has landed in a good spot in Portland and should quietly put up solid production.

name: Johnny Davis
tip: Washington seems to have a type. First Avdija, then Kispert, and now Davis. With all 3 guys playing similar positions, it's hard to see room for one of them to break out.

name: Trey Murphy III
tip: His shot didn't fall last season, and that won't fly next season if he wants to become a steady rotation player.

name: Tre Mann
tip: How much is Williams going to eat into his role next season?

name: TyTy Washington Jr
tip: Houston is light on PGs (sorry, I don't count KPJ as a real PG) so there's an opportunity for TyTy to get minutes in the first half of the season.

name: Ousmane Dieng
tip: NBL stats don't translate well in comparison to college at the best of times, but Dieng's are especially... not great. I see him as a big hit/miss player where he's just as likely going to miss, but if he manages to put it together he's going to put up solid numbers. Strap yourself in though, because it could be rough to start with.

name: Donte DiVincenzo
tip: I'm not sure if he's a fantasy-relevant player in Golden State.

name: Malaki Branham
tip: Branham has the physical attributes to be a quality player and his game should continue to develop as the Spurs training staff do their thing.

name: Kevon Looney
tip: He's still quite young, so there's plenty of room for improvement, seems to be Kerr's preferred option at C, but at some point, Wiseman is going to get minutes after his poor rookie campaign.

name: Precious Achiuwa
tip: A great athlete, but Toronto is collecting ok-but-not-good-enough-to-start calibre centers like they're Pokemon.

name: Isaac Okoro
tip: His defensive ability may not translate into fantasy numbers, and his shot, or willingness to take a shot, hasn't improved enough to lock down a starting role on a good Cleaveland team.

name: Cam Reddish
tip: Isn't getting enough playing time in New York to be fantasy-relevant, but he's somebody to watch where he ends up next season.

name: Terance Mann
tip: Plays well when one of Kawhi or George sits and should see a bigger role heading into next season, but it might take a few seasons before we see a breakout.

name: Oshae Brissett
tip: Will be in the mix for the starting PF spot next season, but we've got an entire off-season for that to change.

name: Goga Bitadze
tip: There's more opportunity for minutes with Sabonis gone, but it's hard seeing him playing too many minutes alongside Turner.

name: James Bouknight
tip: A great scorer and capable rebounder for his size, but Charlotte already has Rozier in a similar role, and we didn't see much of him last season.

name: Isaiah Roby
tip: He looked good in small doses last season, but the opportunity isn't there this season.

name: Montrezl Harrell
tip: His value is propped up by his elite ability to only take a shot when he's 60-65% sure it's going in.

name: Justise Winslow
tip: Showed enough to be a bench player next season.

name: Devonte' Graham
tip: He should be starting the season in New Orleans as the starting PG, but it's far from locked in if a better player becomes available.

name: Chimezie Metu
tip: He'll move back to a consistent bench role next season.

name: Nickeil Alexander-Walker
tip: Still very raw, but the Utah situation doesn't seem as bad as it was when he first got moved to the Jazz.

name: John Wall
tip: Hey, at least Wall gets to play basketball now.

name: Evan Fournier
tip: The move to New York is a better fit than Boston, just don't expect the return of his Orlando production.

name: Aaron Nesmith
tip: Most likely won't see enough playing time to be fantasy-relevant next season.

name: Jeremiah Robinson-Earl
tip: Has the potential to be a capable rotation player.

name: Larry Nance Jr
tip: He's a high-energy per-minute guy, but at this stage of his career, it's hard to see him locking down a starting spot anywhere.

name: Josh Christopher
tip: He's another guy who can score, but does it inefficiently. He does have good defensive instincts, and he's on a Rockets team who will no doubt give him a good stretch of games at some point of the season.

name: Dennis Schroder
tip: Not much long-term appeal in dynasty formats.

name: Cameron Thomas
tip: Cam has all of the tools to be a gunner off the bench, but he doesn't provide much outside of scoring, and Brooklyn already has alot of that.

name: Joe Harris
tip: He provides 3s and shoots a good percentage from the field and at the line, but he doesn't have much upside outside of that.

name: Cedi Osman
tip: His FG% has improved, but he's still best suited for punt FG% builds.

name: Nerlens Noel
tip: Seems like he's destined to be a backup in the NBA.

name: TJ Warren
tip: The TJ bubble has burst - we'll have to wait and see how he looks once he returns from his injury. Don't expect bubble numbers when he does.
injury: Expected to be out until at least Nov 1

name: Kira Lewis Jr
tip: It's just a matter of finding playing time.

name: Luke Kennard
tip: He's still only 25, and the opportunity is there for more minutes with Kawhi injured, but there are people ahead of him on the depth chart.

name: Patty Mills
tip: We might only see a few more seasons of Patty in the league.

name: Shake Milton
tip: Put up nice numbers to start the season, but it's hard seeing a consistent role for him with Harden on the roster.

name: Payton Pritchard
tip: Has already proven to be a spark off the bench and has the tools to be a good role player, but that's where I think his upside ends.

name: Lonnie Walker IV
tip: He's going to try his best to fill the role Munk left in LA.

name: Dwight Powell
tip: Not much upside here.

name: Chris Boucher
tip: Boucher's days of catfishing fantasy managers are over.

name: Corey Kispert
tip: A knock-down shooter who is shooting elite % splits in college, but his game is very one-dimential when it comes to fantasy and his output can generally be found on the waiver wire.
injury: Expected to be out until at least Nov 2

name: Day'Ron Sharpe
tip: Has a limited offensive game, but he's a great rebounder. Brooklyn tends to play small at the C spot, so I'm not sure how much playing time he gets.

name: Maxi Kleber
tip: A good streaming option, but not somebody to rely on.

name: Khem Birch
tip: If his play towards the end of the season is anything to go by he'll be splitting minutes at the C spot next season.

name: Hamidou Diallo
tip: Didn't seize his opportunity at the end of last season and only projects to be a bench player this season in Detroit.

name: Keon Johnson
tip: Great athlete who I'm keeping an eye on to see what his role is like in Portland next season.

name: Eric Paschall
tip: It's debatable how much playing time he'll get in Utah, but it won't be enough to consider rostering him in most dynasty formats.

name: PJ Tucker
tip: Still, only a borderline top-140 guy even if he's playing 35 minutes a night.

name: Zach Collins
tip: Are we still waiting for Zach Collins to do something or has he run out of chances?

name: Marcus Morris Sr
tip: Basically, a streamer when he spot-starts.

name: Juan Toscano-Anderson
tip: A great high-energy guy who does a lot of the dirty stuff needed when on the court with star players. Doesn't chase stats and he's very much a better-in-real-life-than-fantasy type player.

name: Danny Green
tip: A 3-point streamer who's still capable of getting close to a steal and block a game.
injury: Expected to be out until at least Apr 1

name: Furkan Korkmaz
tip: A three-point streamer who offers little else.

name: Duncan Robinson
tip: An elite shooter who doesn't provide anything outside of the scoring and shooting categories.

name: Doug McDermott
tip: Low-upside guy who feels a short-term need. Older than most people think.

name: Kemba Walker
tip: There's a history of undersized point guards not aging well, and his knee injury looks like it's a long-term thing that he'll have to manage through the season.

name: Landry Shamet
tip: Hard to see him become fantasy relevant on a stacked Suns roster.

name: Usman Garuba
tip: Landed in a great spot and should see minutes off the bench this season because of how good he is defensively, but his offensive game is extremely raw.

name: Terrence Ross
tip: Anthony has taken over the role as the primary scorer of the team, and it's taking shots away from Ross.

name: Eric Gordon
tip: There are better 3-point streaming options available. Move on unless he starts getting hot.

name: Jeremy Lamb
tip: Is capable of putting up numbers when given the opportunity to play, but there are better options out there.

name: Xavier Tillman
tip: Not sure how much of Tillman we're going to see next season, but the talent is there.

name: Dean Wade
tip: Played well enough last season to suggest he'll be in the rotation next season, but it won't be enough to make him fantasy relevant.

name: Blake Griffin
tip: Blake dunks again now, but that's not enough to make him rosterable in dynasty formats unless you're in a 30-team league. The addition of Millsap and the return of Aldridge limit his opportunity.

name: Gary Harris
tip: It's time to accept Harris for what he is - a decent real-life NBA player, but a below-average fantasy player. Try and find a believer and move him while he still has some value.

name: TJ McConnell
tip: His value is tied to his high steal numbers, and he hasn't been stealing at an elite level so far this season.

name: Bol Bol
tip: His game translates really well to fantasy if he ever pans out. We'll have to wait and see if his body is up to playing a heavy NBA schedule, and could potentially become a good player off the bench.

name: Daniel Theis
tip: Is he going to find his way back to Boston again at some point this season?

name: Davis Bertans
tip: A one-dimensional fantasy player whose best category is easily found on the waiver wire.

name: Romeo Langford
tip: Needs the ball to be productive, but I'm not sure how well his game translates to fantasy. Seems like his ceiling is being a low-end rotation player.

name: RJ Hampton
tip: Has the size, talent, and ability to be a capable bench player. Is he fantasy relevant? Not so much.

name: Theo Maledon
tip: This year's draft class has dampened Theo's fantasy value, and there's more draft picks coming.

name: Carsen Edwards
tip: A gunner off the bench who'll see minutes on nights when his shot is falling. Not great defensively.

name: Sharife Cooper
tip: A lot of people were expecting him to get drafted earlier, but right now he's best suited as a backup PG in the NBA. I'm not sure how well his game translates to the NBA as a small PG who got to the line a lot in college and didn't hit many 3, but he's got time to develop in Atlanta and I wouldn't be surprised seeing him playing a bigger role on another team.

name: KJ Martin Jr
tip: Showed signs of being a good rotation player off the bench.

name: Eric Bledsoe
tip: We've hit the downward part of Bledsoe's fantasy career.

name: Danilo Gallinari
tip: Capable of still giving you a quality return in PTS and FT% if you're in win-now mode.
injury: Expected to be out until at least Apr 15

name: Facundo Campazzo
tip: A hard one to rank given his age and short-term appeal as he fills a need left by Murray's injury, but he's not somebody to chase in dynasty formats.

name: Saben Lee
tip: He's showing signs of being a good back-up PG behind Hayes in the long-term, but Detroit is oddly deep at the PG spot once everybody is healthy.

name: Kai Jones
tip: He may take a while to develop, but he has the defensive tools and athletic ability that teams are looking for. Somebody to stash for the long-term.

name: Jaden Springer
tip: Springer could be anything. When he's switched on he can put up nice numbers, it's just a matter of consistency and finding a role off the 76ers bench during his rookie season.

name: Reggie Bullock
tip: A short-term streamer, but not somebody to roster long-term in dynasty formats.

name: Hassan Whiteside
tip: I think people are finally starting to accept that he'll be a backup for the rest of his career. Stream him if you need blocks.

name: Thaddeus Young
tip: Should still have some nice short-term value this season depending on the team he plays on (will it be the Spurs?).

name: Trey Lyles
tip: Can put up numbers when he spot-starts. Don't expect him to become a consistent starter though.

name: Serge Ibaka
tip: Added a three-point shot to his game, which will help extend his career, but the Clippers tend to play small and there's another competent C on the roster.

name: Raul Neto
tip: Can't see him being much more than a bench player/spot starter.

name: Josh Green
tip: Has the potential to be a defensive staple in Dallas as a 3&D guy, it'll just take a few seasons for it to happen.

name: Tony Bradley
tip: Will get his run of games to showcase his talent next season, but it's hard to see anybody locking down the C spot in Oklahoma.

name: Nicolas Batum
tip: Has somewhat revived his career in LA, but it's hard to see him finish the season inside the top 100. There are better options out there.

name: Naz Reid
tip: His potential to be a great per-minute guy off the bench.

name: Brandon Goodwin
tip: Won't see much playing time this season, and at best his role is a backup on a team. Not much fantasy upside here.

name: Carmelo Anthony
tip: Somebody to stream when you need points, rebounds, and 3-pointers.

name: Torrey Craig
tip: There are better options available.

name: Dylan Windler
tip: We haven't had a chance to see him string enough games to see what he's capable of, but Cleveland is getting deeper in his position with every draft.

name: Dennis Smith Jr
tip: His days in the NBA might be limited.

name: LaMarcus Aldridge
tip: I really hope LaMarcus knows what he's doing, because this is an unexpected return from retiring last season because of health reasons.

name: DeMarcus Cousins
tip: At this point in his career, he's a fringe spot-starter, and not somebody to consider in dynasty formats.

name: Willy Hernangomez
tip: The experiment was over before it began. Not much to see here unless major injuries happen.

name: Derrick Favors
tip: At this point in his career, he's a spot-starter.

name: Jared Butler
tip: Needs to improve his playmaking and finishing at the rim, but looks like he'll make for a quality backup PG.

name: Miles McBride
tip: Can be a gunner off the bench, but New York already has Quickley for that role?

name: JT Thor
tip: Very raw, but he's worth taking a swing on if you can afford to stash somebody for a few seasons.

name: Isaiah Todd
tip: Lots of upside here as a big man who can shoot, but needs to work things out on the defensive end.

name: Jeff Green
tip: Seems to always find himself in a role where he plays 25 minutes, but there's little upside in his game.

name: Goran Dragic
tip: You have to assume he'll only be in the league for a few more seasons, and while he obviously has little long-term appeal, he can still be capable of producing OK numbers.

name: Ricky Rubio
tip: At this point, he's a nice top-up option if you're looking to compete for a championship next season.
injury: Expected to be out until at least Dec 1

name: DeAndre' Bembry
tip: Bembry hasn't taken the opportunities he has been given so far, and it's hard to see him get many more.

name: Frank Ntilikina
tip: A fresh start is exactly what Frank needs, but the path to minutes doesn't look to be there.

name: Naji Marshall
tip: Hard to see him as a starter in the short term, but should be a nice rotation player coming off the bench.

name: Moses Brown
tip: OKC has too many good options to play at PF next season that I'm worried it's going to be a rotating door again next season where a lot of guys get their run at starting.

name: Jarrett Culver
tip: He's going to find it hard to get playing time this season, but a fresh start in Memphis could be what he's looking for to re-boot his career in the league.

name: Cody Zeller
tip: Zeller's best role is the first big man off the bench, and that's what he'll be in Portland. It just doesn't translate to fantasy relevance.

name: Troy Brown Jr
tip: How long can you stash a guy before it's time to cut ties?

name: Taurean Prince
tip: Hard to see him being anything more than a back-up, but he gets another fresh start in Minnesota.

name: Enes Freedom
tip: His days as a per-minute stud look to have ended, and he's now averaging less than 6 minutes a game.

name: David Nwaba
tip: Seems to always find himself on a roster where he plays 18-20 minutes off the bench, but that's as high as his ceiling gets.

name: Josh Jackson
tip: Somebody you can safely leave on the waiver wire.

name: Ty Jerome
tip: A smart, mature player, but he'll struggle to stop NBA point guards on the defensive end.

name: Alec Burks
tip: He'll go on a hot streak at some point during the season, but his stats are easy to find on the waiver wire.

name: Terence Davis
tip: His path to minutes somehow gets harder with the move to Sacramento, and there are better players that they should prioritize developing.

name: Tomas Satoransky
tip: He seems to have the same role no matter the roster he's on (fringe starter but not somebody you want to roster).

name: Derrick Jones Jr
tip: Won't be fantasy-relevant this season unless something major happens in the off-season.

name: Jalen McDaniels
tip: Has all of the tools to be a nice player, but he's still very raw. A nice stash option.

name: Josh Okogie
tip: His shooting percentages improved from his rookie season and should continue to develop. His upside seems limited, though.

name: Leandro Bolmaro
tip: Has the potential to be a nice role player one day.

name: Elfrid Payton
tip: He's fighting for a backup PG spot with Payne. Hard pass.

name: Aaron Holiday
tip: The best-case scenario is that he becomes the first guard off the bench once everybody is healthy, but he has proved a worthy fill-in starter when given the opportunity.

name: Malachi Flynn
tip: Can't see him being a consistent starter on an NBA team, but he's a well-rounded point guard, and I know better than to write off a player drafted late by Toronto.

name: Dario Saric
tip: He'll be out injured for most of the regular season.

name: Lou Williams
tip: At this stage of his career, he's doing his best work off the court.

name: Svi Mykhailiuk
tip: Is a consistent 3-point shooter when given the chance to play, but his fantasy output is limited and only tied to one category.

name: Moritz Wagner
tip: At best, he's an end of your fantasy roster kind of guy.

name: Juancho Hernangomez
tip: Hasn't shown that he's starter worthy so far in his career.

name: Zeke Nnaji
tip: Still pretty raw, but showed promising signs whenever he played. It's unfortunate that he plays the same position as Denver's best players.

name: Justin Holiday
tip: Has value as a streamer who can fill a short-term need.

name: Paul Millsap
tip: Not much long-term appeal here as he's clearly in the twilight of his career.

name: Austin Rivers
tip: There are better options available.

name: Denzel Valentine
tip: Seems like his ceiling is the 7-8th man on a roster. Only has value in deep league formats.

name: Jeff Teague
tip: It looks like the regression has started. Hard to see him as anything more than a bench player moving forward.

name: Khyri Thomas
tip: He blew up with the handful of games he played for Houston towards the end of the season, but don't expect that to be replicated next season. Realistically he's a fringe starter/bench rotation player.

name: Kris Dunn
tip: Provides little value outside of a steals streaming option when he gets minutes.

name: George Hill
tip: There are better options available.

name: Kenrich Williams
tip: Seems to always find himself in the rotation playing 20-24 minutes a game, but I think his ceiling is capped as a bench rotation player.

name: Joe Ingles
tip: Currently out injured and on vacation in the real estate he owns in Paul George's head.
injury: Expected to be out until at least Jan 4

name: Dante Exum
tip: The Exum experiment travels to Houston, but it's best to keep expectations low.

name: Kevin Knox II
tip: Didn't have a good rookie season, and had a worse second and third seasons.

name: Rodney Hood
tip: A streamer when he gets hot, but not somebody to roster on dynasty teams.

name: Trevor Ariza
tip: It's hard to keep track of what roster he's on these days, but no matter which it is, he won't be fantasy relevant on it.

name: Marquese Chriss
tip: Hard to see a scenario where he becomes fantasy relevant next season.

name: Danuel House Jr
tip: Didn't have the best on-court bubble experience.

name: Tristan Thompson
tip: Seems more interested in avoiding paying child support than playing basketball.

name: Rudy Gay
tip: He's still capable of putting up OK numbers in the short-term, but at his age, there are better options in dynasty formats.

name: Sekou Doumbouya
tip: He didn't get playing time in Detroit so it's hard to see him getting any on a team with championship aspirations.

name: Michael Carter-Williams
tip: Can't see him having too big of a role with a healthy Fultz, RJ, and Cole Anthony to fight for with PG/SG minutes.

name: Cory Joseph
tip: His role will be even smaller next season with Cade coming to Detroit (assuming he won't be with another team).

name: Nemanja Bjelica
tip: He won't be seeing enough minutes in Golden State to be fantasy relevant. There are better options available.

name: Damion Lee
tip: Contributed on a depleted Golden State roster. Hard to see him doing it again.

name: Dwight Howard
tip: A streamer when he spot-starts, but there's better options available.

name: Robin Lopez
tip: Did a nice job playing minutes for an injured Thomas Bryant, but Washington also has Gafford now, so he should move back to his limited minutes bench role next season.

name: DJ Augustin
tip: Has been replaced by Fultz in the starting lineup, and it doesn't look like he'll be getting his spot back any time soon. There are better options available.

name: DeAndre Jordan
tip: We're in the last stage of the twilight of Jordan's career.

name: Dewayne Dedmon
tip: He's not somebody to roster in most formats, but he can still have value when he spot-starts.

name: Willie Cauley-Stein
tip: The move to Dallas doesn't bode well for his fantasy output this season. There should be better options available.

name: Grant Riller
tip: The steal of the draft, but Charlotte is stacked at the PG position.

name: Thon Maker
tip: Not much long-term appeal.

name: Kent Bazemore
tip: Hasn't taken the new opportunity well, and finds himself on the waiver wire in most leagues. There should be better options available.

name: Jabari Parker
tip: He'll continue to hop around the NBA for a few more seasons in backup roles on different teams.

name: Meyers Leonard
tip: Older than most people think and never really broke-out in his 7 seasons in Portland. At this stage in his career, it's hard to see him as anything more than an end-of-bench big man who doesn't hurt either of your percentages.

name: Alex Len
tip: Will continue to bounce around the league in backup roles on different teams - there are better options available.

name: James Johnson
tip: His role tends to be the same on any roster he finds himself on and needs 25+ minutes a game before we consider him.

name: Rajon Rondo
tip: An assists and steals streamer who doesn't provide much else.

name: Zhaire Smith
tip: It's debatable whether we'll see him in the NBA for much longer.

name: Brad Wanamaker
tip: A back-up player at best, and older than you'd expect.

name: Bruno Fernando
tip: He'll continue fighting for a roster spot in the NBA, but he won't be fighting for a roster spot on your fantasy team.

name: Emmanuel Mudiay
tip: Hard to see him finding a spot in the rotation big enough to become fantasy relevant.

name: Omari Spellman
tip: Still needs to get in better shape if he wants to get consistent minutes in the league. He's a wait-and-see to see if he can find himself in a favorable position in the rotation.

name: Ante Zizic
tip: Doesn't have significant upside and has a pretty low block-rate. There are better options available, even in 30-team leagues.

name: Rondae Hollis-Jefferson
tip: He may not be in the NBA for much longer.

name: Cheick Diallo
tip: Can provide some value as a spot-starter if/when he gets a chance to.

name: Noah Vonleh
tip: Seems like he's destined to spend the rest of his career coming off the bench and spot-starting, but he's a capable streaming option when given the minutes.

name: Rodions Kurucs
tip: His days in the NBA look to be numbered.
